from __future__ import annotations

"""
app/mme_scalpx/services/feeds.py

ScalpX MME - production-grade feed normalization and snapshot service.

Ownership
---------
This module owns:
- active-universe-only market data acceptance
- normalization of raw broker payloads into canonical tick events
- per-token latest quote cache for the approved 5-leg universe
- synchronized snapshot assembly for futures + CE/PE ATM/ATM+1
- canonical publication to tick streams and snapshot state hashes
- feed health heartbeat and additive observability
- feeds singleton lock ownership
- runtime entrypoint `run(context)`

This module does NOT own:
- instrument discovery / ATM resolution
- feature computation
- strategy logic
- risk / execution / report logic
- Redis helper implementation
- runtime composition root

Frozen runtime rules
--------------------
- no local instrument discovery
- active universe comes only from RuntimeInstrumentSet
- no raw Redis names outside core.names
- shared-wire truth must be canonical and deterministic
- latest state belongs in hashes; event/history belongs in streams
- publish complete snapshots by default; keep partial buffering internally
- use context.clock, never a process-global clock singleton
- supervised loop must use context.shutdown.wait(...)
"""

